      "id": "head",
      "english": "head",
      "word": "頭",
      "romanized": "atama",
      "grammarNote": "In Japanese, pain is expressed with 'ga itai' (が痛い): 'atama ga itai' (頭が痛い) = my head hurts. Unlike French 'avoir mal à', Japanese uses the subject particle 'ga' and the adjective 'itai' (painful). The body part becomes the subject of the pain.",
      "englishPhrase": "My head hurts.",
      "phrase": "頭が痛いです。",
      "phraseRomanized": "atama ga itai desu",
      "literal": "Head [subj] hurts is."
    },
